                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                          <locus from="3r" to="6v"/>
                          <title type="complete">Prologue</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>According to the catalogue, the text is somewhat shorter than in <ref type="item" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BAVet201#ms_i1.1"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: BAVet201#ms_i1.1</span></ref>.</note>
                          </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                          <locus from="6v" to="9v"/>
                          <title type="complete">First section</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The text contains the first section of E.A.W. Budge's edition, corresponding to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">61 l. 15-63 l. 7</citedRange></bibl>, with some variants and omissions.</note>  
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                          <locus from="9v" to="12r"/>
                          <title type="complete">Third section</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The text contains the first part of the third section of E.A.W. Budge's edition, corresponding to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">67 l. 2-68 l. 4</citedRange></bibl>, then, after few magic names, it concludes like in the second part of the third section, i.e.
                            <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">71 l. 8</citedRange></bibl>.
                          </note>  
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4">
                          <locus from="12r" to="13r"/>
                          <title type="complete">Third section (continuation)</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The text contains the last part of the third section of E.A.W. Budge's edition, corresponding to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">71 l. 8-last line</citedRange></bibl>.</note>  
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.5">
                          <locus from="13r" to="15r"/>
                          <title type="complete">Fourth section</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The text contains the first part of the fourth section of E.A.W. Budge's edition, corresponding to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">73 l. 2-74 l. 22</citedRange></bibl>, with some variants and omissions.</note>  
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.6">
                          <locus from="15r" to="16r"/>
                          <title type="complete">First prayer for the heavenly journey</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                            <choice><sic>ወለማርያም</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ወበማርያም፡</corr></choice> ወላዲትከ፡ በ፲ወ፪ ነቢያት፡ በ፲፪ ሐዋርያት፡ 
                            ወበ፲፻፡ ቢጽ፡ ወ፸ወ፪ አርድእት፡ በ፳ወ፬ ካህናተ፡ ሰማይ፡ ወበ <supplied reason="omitted">፲</supplied>፭ ነቢያት፡ ወ፭፻ ቢጽ፡ ከመ፡ ትምሐረኒ፡ ወትሣሃለኒ፡
                            <choice><sic>ለአመትኪ</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ለአመትከ፡</corr></choice> አመተ፡ ማርያም<supplied reason="omitted">፨</supplied>
                          </explicit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.7">
                          <locus from="16r" to="16v"/>
                          <title type="complete">Second prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The prayer includes the following invocation:
                            <q xml:lang="gez">በ፼ አእላፍ፡ መላእክት፡ ተማኅፀ<supplied reason="omitted">ን</supplied>ኩ፡ አነ፡</q>.
                          </note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.8">
                          <locus from="16v" to="17r"/>
                          <title type="complete">Third prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The prayer includes the following invocation:
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ሐዳሳተ፡ <supplied reason="omitted">ሰማይ፡</supplied> ወሐዳሳተ፡ ምድር፡ ክቡር፡ ንጉሥ፡ አመ፡ ይነግሥ፡ ሎሙ፡ መሐረኒ፡ መሐሪ፡</q>.
                          </note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.9">
                          <locus from="17r" to="17v"/>
                          <title type="complete">Fourth prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The prayer includes the following invocation:
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ሱራፌል፡ ወኪሩቤል፡ ይነሥዕዋ፡ ለ<supplied reason="omitted">ነ</supplied>ፍስየ፡ መላእክተ፡ ጽልመት፡ 
                              <surplus>ወ</surplus>ኢይሬ<supplied reason="omitted">እ</supplied>ይዋ፡</q>.
                          </note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.10">
                          <locus from="17v" to="18r"/>
                          <title type="complete">Fifth prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The prayer includes the following invocation:
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ሚካኤል፡ ወገብርኤል፡ ሰአሉ፡ ለነ፡ ጰራቅሊጦስ፡ ናዛዜ፡ ኵሉ፡ ዓለም፡ በይ<supplied reason="omitted">ይ</supplied>ቲ፡
                            ዕለት፡ መሐሪ፡ ወመሐራ፡ ለነፍስየ፡</q>, cp.
                            <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">76 ll. 8-12</citedRange></bibl>.
                          </note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.11">
                          <locus from="18r" to="19r"/>
                          <title type="complete">Sixth prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>Cp.  <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">76 ll. 16-21</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.12">
                          <locus from="19r" to="20v"/>
                          <title type="complete">Seventh prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>Cp.  <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">76 ll. 25-30, 77 ll. 1-5</citedRange></bibl>, to which an invocation for the liberatation from the hell is added.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.13">
                          <locus from="20v" to="24r"/>
                          <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6967PrayerPassion">Prayer on the Passion of Jesus Christ, which Jesus
          revealed to Matilda, Bridget and Elizabeth</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                            በስመ፡ አብ፡ <gap reason="omitted" resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices"/> ንጽሕፍ<supplied reason="omitted">፡</supplied> ዜና፡ ሕማማቲሁ፡ 
                            <choice><sic>ወአምላከነ፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ለአምላክነ</corr></choice> ወመድኃኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡
                            ዘ<surplus>ለ<del rend="expunctuated">ዕ</del>ሌከ</surplus>ከሠትከ፡ ሎን፡ ለ፵ አንስት<supplied reason="omitted">፡</supplied> እለ፡ ይሰመያ፡ ሰሎሜ፡ <sic>ወዮሴፍ፤</sic> ወማርያም፡
                            <choice><sic>መግዊላዊት፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">መግደላዊት፡</corr></choice> ወኤልሳቤጥ፡
                            </incipit>
                          <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                            በቅዱስ፡ ስንዱን፡ ሥጋከ፡ ዘተገንዘ፡ በእደ፡ ዮሴፍ፡ ወኒቆዲሞስ፡ ድኅረ፡ አውረድዎ፡ እመስቀል፡ ሥመር፡ እግዚኦ፡ በርኅራኄከ፡ ወበትንሣኤከ፤ ወበተቀብሮትከ፤
                            <choice><sic>ዘየሐቱ፤</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ዘያሐዩ፤</corr></choice> ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን፡
                            ድሙር፡ ሥቃያቲከ፡ ፼፼ አ<add place="above">ስ</add>ተርአያ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ለማርያም፡ ፍፃሜሁ፡ ለልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ ተፈጸመ፡ ልፋፈ፤ ጽድቅ፨
                          </explicit>
                        </msItem>                        
                      </msItem>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                        <locus from="25r" to="25v"/>
                        <title type="complete">Narration of the torments suffered by Jesus Christ</title>
                        <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                          ፶፡ ወ፪ ጊዜያተ፡ ሰብሕዎ፡ ወ<supplied reason="omitted">ወ</supplied>ሀብዎ፡  <choice><sic>ባሐብ</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ባሐከ፡</corr></choice> 
                          ወነጽይዎ፡ ጽሕሞ፡ ወጸጕረ፡ ርእሱ፡ ወዘበጥዎ፡ <choice><sic>እንግዳሁ፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">እንግድኣሁ፡</corr></choice> 
                        </incipit>
                          <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                            ፲ወ፪ ዘወረቅዎ፡ ምራቀ፡ አይሁድ፡ <choice><sic>ቍስላተ፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ቍስላት፡</corr></choice> ዘነበሩ፡ ቦቱ፡ 
                            ፲ወ፪<surplus>፱</surplus>፼፳፻<supplied reason="omitted">፡</supplied> <choice><sic>ወእለ</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ወእለ፡</corr></choice> 
